\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 ## Setting Up Pi A (Server + Display)
\f1\b0 \cf4 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 1.\cf4 \strokec4  Flash Raspberry Pi OS (64-bit, Desktop) to the SD card\cb1 \
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 2.\cf4 \strokec4  Connect the 7" display\cb1 \
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 3.\cf4 \strokec4  SSH in and clone your repo to \cf6 \strokec6 `~/livedoodle`\cf4 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 4.\cf4 \strokec4  Install Python deps: \cf6 \strokec6 `pip install -r requirements.txt`\cf4 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 5.\cf4 \strokec4  Install the systemd service (see above)\cb1 \
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 6.\cf4 \strokec4  Set up Chromium to auto-launch in kiosk mode on boot by adding this to \cf6 \strokec6 `~/.config/lxsession/LXDE-pi/autostart`\cf4 \strokec4 :\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \cb3    ```\cb1 \
\cb3    @xset s off\cb1 \
\cb3    @xset -dpms\cb1 \
\cb3    @xset s noblank\cb1 \
\cb3    @bash -c 'sleep 5 && chromium --kiosk --noerrdialogs --disable-infobars http://localhost:8000/display'\cb1 \
\cb3    ```\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 7.\cf4 \strokec4  Install and configure Cloudflare Tunnel to expose port 8000 publicly\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \cb3 ---\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 ## Setting Up Pi B (Camera)
\f1\b0 \cf4 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 1.\cf4 \strokec4  Flash Raspberry Pi OS (64-bit, Lite) to the SD card\cb1 \
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 2.\cf4 \strokec4  Connect the HQ camera module\cb1 \
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 3.\cf4 \strokec4  Write a small Python script (\cf6 \strokec6 `stream.py`\cf4 \strokec4 ) using picamera2 that:\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \cb3    \cf5 \strokec5 -\cf4 \strokec4  Serves JPEG snapshots at \cf6 \strokec6 `http://0.0.0.0:8080/?action=snapshot`\cf4 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cb3    \cf5 \strokec5 -\cf4 \strokec4  Accepts POST requests to \cf6 \strokec6 `/controls`\cf4 \strokec4  for adjusting camera settings (brightness, contrast, saturation, exposure, gain)\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 **AI prompt for stream.py:**
\f1\b0 \cf4 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \cb3 "Write a Python HTTP server using picamera2 that serves a single JPEG snapshot at GET /?action=snapshot and accepts camera control adjustments via POST /controls (JSON body with keys: brightness, contrast, saturation, exposure, gain, auto). When 'auto' is true, recreate the camera to re-enable auto-exposure. Run on port 8080."\cb1 \
\
\cb3 ---\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 ## Cloudflare Tunnel Setup
\f1\b0 \cf4 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 1.\cf4 \strokec4  Create a free Cloudflare account and add your domain (or use a free .trycloudflare.com URL)\cb1 \
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 2.\cf4 \strokec4  Install \cf6 \strokec6 `cloudflared`\cf4 \strokec4  on Pi A\cb1 \
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 3.\cf4 \strokec4  Run \cf6 \strokec6 `cloudflared tunnel login`\cf4 \strokec4  and \cf6 \strokec6 `cloudflared tunnel create livedoodle`\cf4 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 4.\cf4 \strokec4  Configure the tunnel to point to \cf6 \strokec6 `http://localhost:8000`\cf4 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 5.\cf4 \strokec4  Set it to run as a service so it starts on boot\cb1 \
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 6.\cf4 \strokec4  In \cf6 \strokec6 `main.py`\cf4 \strokec4 , use \cf6 \strokec6 `--proxy-headers`\cf4 \strokec4  with uvicorn so the real visitor IP comes through from Cloudflare headers\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \cb3 ---\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 ## Development Workflow
\f1\b0 \cf4 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 -\cf4 \strokec4  Make changes locally on your Mac\cb1 \
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 -\cf4 \strokec4  SCP templates directly to the Pi for instant preview (no restart needed for HTML/CSS/JS changes):\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \cb3   ```bash\cb1 \
\cb3   \cf7 \strokec7 scp templates/draw.html user@PI_IP:~/livedoodle/templates/draw.html\cf4 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cb3   ```\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 -\cf4 \strokec4  Changes to \cf6 \strokec6 `main.py`\cf4 \strokec4  require restarting the service:\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \cb3   ```bash\cb1 \
\cb3   \cf7 \strokec7 scp main.py user@PI_IP:~/livedoodle/main.py\cf4 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cb3   \cf7 \strokec7 ssh user@PI_IP \cf6 \strokec6 "sudo systemctl restart livedoodle"\cf4 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cb3   ```\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 -\cf4 \strokec4  Run locally for development:\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \cb3   ```bash\cb1 \
\cb3   \cf7 \strokec7 uvicorn main:app --reload\cf4 \cb1 \strokec4 \
\cb3   ```\cb1 \
\
\cb3 ---\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

